{
  "explanation": "The defendant, functioning as an accountant, abused a significant position of trust to embezzle $25,000 from their employer. Mitigating factors include the defendant's lack of any prior criminal record and their efforts toward making partial restitution before sentencing. Outbursts from spectators in the courtroom are legally irrelevant and carry no weight in the sentencing decision. Balancing the serious breach of fiduciary duty against the defendant's clean record and proactive repayment efforts, a short period of incarceration is appropriate to serve as a deterrent, alongside order of full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
